  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nanvil 0.1.0 (d70aea4 2023-02-15T20:58:12.05498163Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil --prune-history 100 --steps-tracing --silent --port 38181\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nValues of fields in the response of the `eth_getTransactionByHash` JSON-RPC call do not seem to reflect the values set in the `eth_sendTransaction` call. In my case, transaction `type` and `maxPriorityFeePerGas` fields seem to be different. Please see https://gist.github.com/michprev/8f149307ecbdf03ae4ff93e7707a4307 for the JSON-RPC communication log.",
