    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think I found the cause of this issue.\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/ecddbdb5081d9bce725d91a62d7ebc96f2701616/anvil/core/src/eth/transaction/mod.rs#L99\r\n\r\nI am sending only `max_priority_fee_per_gas` in my requests but this line only checks `max_fee_per_gas` which is `None`. This way, the transaction ends up to be recognized as a type 1 transaction (EIP-2930). It would be better to check both `max_priority_fee_per_gas` and `max_fee_per_gas`. I think I can make a PR for that.\r\n\r\nAlso, it is somewhat strange to send the `maxPriorityFeePerGas` and `maxFeePerGas` fields in the response of `eth_getTransactionByHash` for type 0 and type 1 transactions. I think this can be considered a bug too.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/ecddbdb5081d9bce725d91a62d7ebc96f2701616/anvil/src/eth/api.rs#L945-L952\r\n\r\nThis call sets the `is_eip1559` argument to `true` no matter the real transaction type.\r\n",
