    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "From my understanding, `effectiveGasPrice` in a tx receipt can be used to retrieve the actual \"gas price\" used for a transaction, which is something that is currently assigned to `gasPrice` in lines 2031 - 2036. A tx receipt can only be retrieved for a mined tx. Using `max_fee_per_gas` as the gas price for a not yet mined tx does not seem right to me anyway.\r\n\r\nSo I would vote for removing the `gasPrice` field in type 2 (EIP-1559) transactions.",
