    "body": "> Do we want to stick up strictly with the specification (i.e. remove the gasPrice field for EIP-1559 txs) or follow Hardhat and leave the value of gasPrice as it is currently implemented?\r\n\r\nI guess we can also just leave it as is.\r\n\r\n> Also, it is somewhat strange to send the maxPriorityFeePerGas and maxFeePerGas fields in the response of eth_getTransactionByHash for type 0 and type 1 transactions. I think this can be considered a bug too.\r\n\r\nagree.\r\n\r\n> So I would vote for removing the gasPrice field in type 2 (EIP-1559) transactions.\r\n\r\nhmm this seems to be included:\r\n\r\nSome random tx\r\n```\r\ncast rpc eth_getTransactionByHash 0x794b012a17c450294bcc5b52da87cb38c6f1bd8514ca7abe5945e68a44b24b4f --rpc-url \"<api-url>\" | jq  \r\n``` \r\n\r\n```\r\n\"gasPrice\": \"0x4a2d6217c\",\r\n\"maxFeePerGas\": \"0x4a2d6217c\",\r\n\"maxPriorityFeePerGas\": \"0x0\",\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
